<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8724&amp;p=91469#p91469"><![CDATA[
I have a Japanese Super Famicom with damaged OAM (object attribute memory, basically what tells it where sprites go and how to flip them.)<br /><br />As a result, you don't read back what you wrote to OAM, and sprites get all mixed up and flipped oddly.<br /><br />Not much can be done about it, the OAM is inside one of the PPU chips.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=375">byuu</a> — Sat Mar 17, 2012 11:05 pm</p><hr />
